  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Operations Manager",
  "description": "<ol><li><strong>Operations\n     Management:</strong> Overseeing the day-to-day operations of the restaurant,\n     ensuring smooth functioning of all departments such as kitchen, dining\n     area, and delivery services.</li><li><strong>Staff\n     Management:</strong> Hiring, training, scheduling, and supervising staff\n     members, including chefs, cooks, servers, bartenders, and hosts/hostesses.\n     Ensuring that all employees adhere to restaurant policies and procedures.</li><li><strong>Customer\n     Service:</strong> Ensuring high levels of customer satisfaction by addressing\n     customer complaints or concerns promptly and effectively, and maintaining\n     a welcoming and hospitable atmosphere.</li><li><strong>Financial\n     Management:</strong> Managing the restaurant's budget, including monitoring\n     expenses, and ensuring profitability, inventory management and controlling\n     food and beverage costs.</li><li><strong>Health\n     and Safety Compliance:</strong> Ensuring that the restaurant complies with\n     health and safety regulations, including food safety standards,\n     cleanliness, and proper sanitation practices.</li><li><strong>Marketing\n     and Promotion:</strong> Work with marketing department to develop and implement\n     marketing strategies to attract customers, increase sales, and promote\n     special events or promotions.</li><li><strong>Inventory\n     and Supply Chain Management:</strong> Managing inventory levels, ordering\n     supplies, and coordinating with vendors to ensure timely delivery of fresh\n     ingredients and other necessary items.</li><li><strong>Administrative\n     Tasks:</strong> Handling administrative duties such as employees attendance,\n     perform goods receiving and keying in purchase orders into system.</li></ol>",
